    <h1>28 HONG KONG STREET</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201025/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-25"><time>2020-10-25</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE FOOD &amp; DRINK</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Now on the menu: Amer­i­can-style dishes like fried chicken</p>
    <p>Where: 28 Hong Kong Street</p>
    <p>Open: Tues­days to Satur­days, 5 to 7pm</p>
    <p>Info: Reser­va­tions are re­quired – What­sApp 8318-0328 or e-mail fin­dus@28hks.com</p>
    <p>Bet­ter known as a lively late-night Amer­i­can-style cock­tail bar in the pre-Covid-19 days, 28HKS re­tains its hip-hop playlists – al­beit played softer – and world-class cock­tails, while now serv­ing up a ro­tat­ing menu of dishes for its Proper Din­ner, with recipes by in­dus­try-lead­ing Amer­i­can chefs.</p>
    <p>The cur­rent menu fea­tures dishes from Mi­ami’s Sweet Lib­erty Drinks & Sup­ply Com­pany, in­clud­ing Michy’s Fried Chicken with mashed pota­toes and gravy with a side of feta wa­ter­melon salad, and but­ter­milk fried seabass with coleslaw and roasted toma­toes.</p>
    <p>The recipes come di­rectly from the Florida bar’s James Beard Award-win­ning chef Michelle Bern­stein. Dishes are priced at $25++ to $30++.</p>
    <p>They can be paired with cock­tails, also from Sweet Lib­erty, made with Michter’s bour­bon whiskey – such as the cof­fee-and-rum-based Beast of Bour­bon and the grape­fruit and honey-based Brown Derby.</p>

